# Git commit policy

After completing any code changes in this repository:

1. Commit all relevant changes — do not leave work uncommitted when a task is done.
2. Author must always be **Lucas Zhang \<lucaszhang1118@gmail.com\>**.
3. Use the project script from repo root:
   ```powershell
   powershell -NoProfile -File .\scripts\commit.ps1 -StageAll -Push -Message "..." -Body "..."
   ```
4. Push to `origin` on the current branch unless the user explicitly says not to push.
5. Do not skip commits unless the user explicitly cancels a task with no changes to keep.

Only skip committing when there are literally no file changes to commit.
